$interpreted:
Yan-Bo: Weave a circle round him thrice, 
And close your eyes with holy dread 
For he on honey-dew hath fed, 
And drunk the milk of Paradise.
Yan-Bo: Hmm〜beautiful... Maple Lake, this place is?
Yan-Bo: An inebriating view, I did not think this place would have. A trip in vain, this was not.
Hestia: Damn you, take that!
Yan-Bo: The matter, what seems to be?
Yan-Bo: Unsuitable for this beautiful scenery, this austere attitude is. From whence does it come?
Hestia: Oh crap!
Yan-Bo: Enough.  Already decided, the battle is. No need to kill, there is.
Yan-Bo: Listen you will not. Blame the old man, you shall not.
Hestia: Finally! Got them the hell outta here!
Yan-Bo: Already lost, they have. Kill every last one, is this truly worth it?
Hestia: You don't understand. Every last one of these frogodiles is a rotten egg. All they do is attack the creatures of Maple Lake and gobble them up.
Hestia: It'd be best for Maple Lake to kick them all out of here!
Yan-Bo: Ah, is that so?
Hestia: I want to thank you for saving me. My name's Hestia. Sir, what's your name?
Yan-Bo: Yan-Bo, my name is. Foreigner to this place, I am. Just lucky to be passing through, I was.
Platypus: Qua kekekek!
Hestia: An egg!? It's not those frogodiles', is it?
Yan-Bo: Ideal, this is not. Ran away, its whole family has. Best course of action is what?
Hestia: Sir, I can't really understand what you are saying...
Yan-Bo: Apologies. Rephrase this, I must. What I meant is: With this egg, what ought to be done?
Hestia: Don't bother with it. Just leave it here.
Yan-Bo: No, no.  If prematurely destroyed the egg is, because a caring family it lacks; a loss of innocent life, this is.
Hestia: Then what should we do? They ran so far away and we don't know if they'll come back or not.
Hestia: It's hatching!?
Yan-Bo: Young in age, yet so ruthless already......
Hestia: Damnit, Mister Yan-Bo! Give him to me; let me throw him away!
Yan-Bo: Is this so? So small, it is. Without care, to death, it shall surely go.
Hestia: But... just look at how mean he is.
Hestia: If he stays, he'll be exactly like his tribe, attacking the creatures of Maple Lake and disturbing the peace here!
Yan-Bo: A rotten child, must he be? His bad tendencies, with education, improve them, can we not?
Yan-Bo: Fate between us, indeed this is.
Yan-Bo: An orphan, this child became. Responsibility, I too have. Raise him, I shall.
Hestia: What? He's a frogodile. What if he grows up and eats you?
Yan-Bo: Other seeds fell into good soil and produced grain, growing up and increasing and yielding thirtyfold
Hestia: Mister Yan-Bo, you're saying confusing things again.
Yan-Bo: What I meant is: A blank slate, a child is. His virtuous side will show, if a good education he is given.
Yan-Bo: You think so too, right?
